title: Suspect in custody in connection to North Austin fatal shooting
content:
A suspect is now in custody in connection to a shooting in North Austin. Police have arrested 42-year-old Osiel Benitez. The shooting happened on May 8 on North Lamar.
Investigators say 39-year-old Riogberto Jose died when a shooter began firing into a crowd. The shooter fired the shots because police he and another man got into a fight.
Three others were wounded and were taken to the hospital. Their current conditions are not known.
No further details about the shooting have been released.
